<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Three" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Three,</orth> two and one: <bibl n="shak. ven 1064" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1064</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 104.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 104, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 211" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.283" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 53</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.136.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.136.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 136</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 2, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.327" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 327</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.110" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.362.50" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 362</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 278</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 39</bibl> etc. etc. <emph>the picture of</emph> '<emph>we t.</emph>' <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 17</bibl> (Malone: a common sign, in which two wooden heads are exhibited with this inscription under it, <emph>'We three loggerheads be';</emph> the spectator being supposed to make the third).<lb />Substantively: <cit><quote>now here is t. studied,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I always took t. --s for nine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.495" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 495</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>by twos and --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.438" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 438</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these four --s of herdsmen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.344" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 344</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>one t. of them hath danced before the king,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.344" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 344</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>by ones, by twos, and by --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 47</bibl></cit>.
<lb />Misapplied by Evans for <cit><quote>third:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 142</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>